&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;The 
questions&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;1)Thermal imaging 
cameras and infrared film produce similar results when it comes to detecting 
heat.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. True &lt;SPAN 
style="mso-spacerun: yes"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;b. False&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;2) It is possible to 
accurately detect problems inside an electrical panel or other such equipment 
without removing the cover.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. True &lt;SPAN 
style="mso-spacerun: yes"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;b. 
False&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;3) The emissivity 
correction value of copper is:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. .68 &lt;SPAN 
style="mso-spacerun: yes"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;b. 
.05&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;c. .10 &lt;SPAN 
style="mso-spacerun: yes"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;d. Any of the 
above&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;4) Which of the 
following is essential information to help you assess the repair priority of a 
component found with your infrared camera?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. Age of the 
component&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;b. Criticality of the 
component&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;c. Temperature of the 
component&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;d. The wave band being 
detected&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;5) What standards are 
available to guide a thermographer who is inspecting electrical and mechanical 
equipment?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. NFPA 
70A&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;b. ASTM 
1934&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;table width="400" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0"&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;img src="http://media.noria.com/sites/archive_images/backup_200605_Applied-Reil---IR-Figure-4.jpg" width="200" height="153"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Photo 4. The containers contain water at the same hot temperature, but the surface temperatures vary widely.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;  &lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;c. ISO 
  18425&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

  &lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;d. There are no 
  standards relating to thermography&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;6) You are considering 
the purchase of an infrared camera that will be used primarily for indoor 
machine inspections at close distances (up to 10 feet from the component). Which 
of the following specifications is important in your 
choice?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. Field of 
view&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;b. Spatial 
resolution&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;c. Minimum 
focus&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;d. All of the 
above&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;7) You see a âhot 
spotâ on a heavily oxidized overhead disconnect switch on the plantâs incoming 
power pole. When you measure the temperature with your camera, it reads minus-5 
degrees F. The air temperature is 50 degrees F, the sun is out and the sky is 
blue. What is the probable explanation?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. You had set 
emissivity to .9 instead of the recommended .68&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;

&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;b. You are probably 
seeing a reflection of the sun instead of a real hot spot&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;c. You are not working 
within the limits of your cameraâs measurement resolution&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;d. The wind has cooled 
the hot connection&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;8)Thermography is not 
a useful technology for diagnosing problems in rotating 
equipment.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;a. True &lt;SPAN 
style="mso-spacerun: yes"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;b. False&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;THE 
ANSWERS&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;1) b. 
False&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Infrared film, which 
can be used in conventional visual cameras, is sensitive to much shorter 
wavelengths of electromagnetic radiation than a longwave thermal imaging system. 
Imagine a room with no light and everything having a temperature of 30 degrees C 
(86Â°F). If we began to heat an electric hotplate in the room, we could see it 
with an infrared camera when it reached 30.01 C (86.02Â°F). To see the same 
object with infrared film, it would need to be heated to 230 C (446Â°F). Of 
course, by the time it reaches about 550 C (1022Â°F), we can see it with our eyes 
as it glows a dull red.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;

&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Despite the 
differences in technologies, it isnât uncommon for people to want to try the 
less expensive route of using infrared film to locate their maintenance 
problems. Try it if you must, but infrared film will never replace an infrared 
camera.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;2) b. 
False&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;In this age of 
Internet pseudo-science, many people have come to believe you can âsee through 
wallsâ with infrared cameras. However, it is not possible; in fact, it is also 
impossible to see through the clear plastic âtouch-safeâ panels found inside 
many control cabinets.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;To reliably detect 
problems, enclosures must be opened and panels removed. A hot spot inside may 
eventually produce enough heat to produce a thermal signature on the unopened 
enclosure, but in many cases, it still canât be detected due to ambient 
conditions. Even if it is detected, the internal&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;damage is, by then, 
typically well advanced. The thermal image (Photo 2) shows approximately a 15Â°C 
(27 F) rise over normal on the outside of the enclosure. As can be seen in the 
visual image (Photo 3) of the interior, the copper busbar had heated to the 
point where it was severely damaged.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Infrared transparent windows and 
view ports may offer an alternative means of seeing inside enclosures without 
opening the covers. The plastic âtouch safeâ interior panels are still a 
problem, regardless, as they are opaque to infrared 
radiation.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;3) d. Any of the 
above&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;The visual equivalent 
of this question would be to ask âWhat is the color blue?â There are many 
choices. The exact surface of copper can vary just as widely as the color blue 
and, in each case, a different emissivity correction value would be needed. Even 
when we define the surface more precisely, such as âhighly polished copper,â 
there can be significant variations in emissivity.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Does it matter? Yes. 
Especially for a surface with a relatively low emissivity, using an incorrect 
value can make a large difference in the temperature value obtained. Too many 
thermographers believe, incorrectly, that if they simply input the right 
correction value from a table (some of which may be in the camera software 
itself), all will be well. These tables may be useful as guides, but they canât 
replace critical thinking.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;

&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;4) b. Criticality of 
the component&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Itâs not uncommon to 
find a wide range of temperature indications of abnormal situations. As an 
example, all of the containers in the thermal image (Photo 4) contain water at 
the same hot temperature, but the surface temperatures vary widely for each. The 
same is true of the machinery we look at during an 
inspection.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Temperature and 
thermal patterns are useful information, but without an understanding of the 
criticality of the asset, no rational determination can be made of how to 
prioritize a finding. In fact, conditions can easily be such that an indication 
of serious concern may be so subtle as to be undetectable. Take great care, 
therefore, to ensure that conditions are sufficient to locate any anomalies that 
might exist.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Once detected, many 
other indicators, including temperature, age and criticality, among others, will 
probably be used to prioritize an appropriate course of 
action.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;5) b. ASTM 
1934&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;âE1934-99a(2005)e1 
Standard Guide for Examining Electrical and Mechanical Equipment with Infrared 
Thermographyâ from ASTM International was written specifically to address the 
needs of maintenance thermographers. In fact, it is currently being revised into 
two separate standard guides, one for electrical inspections and one for 
mechanical. The current document, which provides a strong foundation for 
condition monitoring-related IR inspections, is available at www.astm.org. In 
the near future, also expect to see standards for infrared mechanical 
inspections from the International Standards&lt;o:p&gt; &lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Organization 
(ISO).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;6) d. All of the 
above&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Potential purchasers 
of infrared cameras often donât fully understood the camera âspec sheet.â Sales 
people can easily make you believe a specification (one their system has) is 
critical while glossing over other details. Itâs vital to understand what each 
specification actually means and how it affects your use of the camera in your 
plant.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;

&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Spatial resolution is 
getting plenty of press lately as newer, lower-cost cameras come on the market 
with lower resolution than has ever been offered. In fact, many of these perform 
quite well for many (but not all) condition monitoring (CM) applications. If you 
can get closer to the equipment being inspected, resolution may not be an 
issue.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Resolution also 
affects field of view (FOV). This is the area you see though the lens at a given 
distance. In many instances, access is limited, and knowing what the minimum 
focus distance is may be critical to success. The bottom line is to understand 
specifications and your real needs before you look at what camera to 
buy.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;7) c. You are not 
working within the limits of your cameraâs measurement 
resolution&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Itâs most likely that 
you are averaging the temperature of the clear sky, which is extremely cold, 
with the hot spot because you are working outside the resolution limits of the 
camera. If you can move closer or use a telephoto lens, you may be able to 
improve the measurement. But if not, remember that the hot spot is actually hot 
even if you canât accurately measure it.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"&gt;&lt;B 
style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;8) b. 
False&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;While the 
interpretation of thermal signatures of rotating equipment can present 
challenges, especially to thermographers who arenât qualified, the technology 
plays an invaluable role in many world-class CM programs. Thermography is best 
used to locate anomalies. Once detected, temperature values may be useful as 
well, but typically, information from other technologies (vibration, ultrasound 
and tribology) will also be important to the analysis.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;How is your IR 
IQ?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Here is the suggested 
scoring scale:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;8 correct = Red 
hot!&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;

&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;6-7 = Warm and 
learning&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;4-5 = Lukewarm and 
needs heating&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Fewer than 4 = Too 
cold for comfort&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;Now your real-life 
test continues. There are a number of sources of information about thermography 
available, including this magazine. But you must learn to think critically and 
constantly challenge yourself to do better if you ever hope to make thermography 
pay its full return.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P &gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;I 
style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;&lt;SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;John Snell is the 
founder and president of Snell Infrared. The company works with all major 
suppliers of IR systems to provide their customers with training, while 
remaining independent of the sale of any particular product. To learn more, call 
800-636-9820 or visit &lt;A 
href="http://www.snellinfrared.com"&gt;www.snellinfrared.com&lt;/A&gt;.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/infrared_thermography/~4/gGKGCMhRpCA" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
